text: Stung Treng is a province in Cambodia. The capital city is also named Stung Treng. The Mekong River bisects the province. It one of the few provinces where you can see the rare and endangered Irrawaddy dolphins. There are 5 districts and 1 municipality: *Borei O'Svay Sen Chey *Sesan *Siem Bouk *Siem Pang *Stung Treng Municipality *Thala Barivat ==References== Category:Provinces of Cambodia Category:Establishments in Cambodia Category:1907 establishments in Asia
